                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Fine and fairly regular.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red (vivid vermilion).</seg> Scribe: Gabra Māryām.
                        Gabra Māryām is mentioned as the scribe in the colophon. <date
                           notBefore="1850" notAfter="1899" cert="low">Second half of the 19th
                           century (?).</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>
                              <foreign xml:lang="gez">ለዓ፡</foreign> for <foreign xml:lang="gez"
                                 >ለዓለም፡</foreign>
                           </item>
                           <item>
                              <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዓ፡/ዓለ፡</foreign> for <foreign xml:lang="gez"
                                 >ዓለም፡</foreign>
                           </item>
                           <item>
                              <foreign xml:lang="gez">አ፡/አሜ፡</foreign> for <foreign xml:lang="gez"
                                 >አሜን፡</foreign>
                           </item>
                           <item>
                              <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሰ፡/ሰላ፡</foreign> for <foreign xml:lang="gez"
                                 >ሰላም፡</foreign>
                           </item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; the name of the protagonist and other
                           saints (e.g. <locus target="#3va"/>, <locus target="#6rb"/>, <locus
                              target="#8va"/>, <locus target="#13va"/>, etc.); the name of the owner
                           and members of his family (e.g. <locus target="#24va"/>, <locus
                              target="#32va"/>, <locus target="#35rb"/>; a few lines alternating
                           with black lines on the incipit page of <ref target="#ms_i1"/> (<locus
                              target="#3r"/>), <ref target="#ms_i2"/> (<locus target="#28rb"/>),
                              <ref target="#ms_i3"/> (<locus target="#36r"/>); incipit of the
                           subsections in <ref target="#ms_i1"/> and <ref target="#ms_i2"/>; the
                           word <foreign xml:lang="gez">salām</foreign> “salutation” and its
                           abbreviation in <ref target="#ms_i3"/>; elements of the punctuation signs
                           and text dividers; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">
                        <locus from="26v" to="27r"/>
                        <seg type="script">The quality of the handwriting becomes less regular, more
                           right-sloping on <locus from="26v" to="27r"/>.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>

                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#3r"/>
                        <desc>(incipit page): elaborate coloured (red, yellow, green and blue)
                           ornamental band with two pairs of ailes; interlaces, zoomorphic motifs
                           (two birds at the top).</desc>
                     </decoNote>

                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2">
                        <locus target="#2v"/>
                        <desc>
                           <persName ref="PRS1906Ananyao"/>: Front view of <persName
                              ref="PRS1906Ananyao"/> praying, with a <term key="prayerstaff"/> in
                           his left hand and a rosary in his right hand.</desc>
                        <q xml:lang="gez">በከመ፡ ጸለየ፡ አቡነ፡ አናንያ፡ ጻድቅ፡ ወሰማዕት፡</q>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en">How the righteous and martyr ʾabuna ʾAnānyā
                           prayed.</foreign>
                     </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>

                  <additions>
                     <list>

                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#39vb"/>
                           <desc type="OwnershipNote"/>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#39vb"/> ዝመ<sic>ዝ</sic>ሐፍ፡ ዘልጅ፡ ገብረ፡ ኪዳን፡ ወአቡሁ፡ ገብረ፡
                              ሚካኤል፡ ወእሙ፡ ወለተ፡ ማርያም፡ ወአኃዊሁ፡ ገብረ፡ ማርያም፡ ፍሬ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ገብረ፡ መስቀል፡ ገብረ፡ ስላሴ፡
                              ወለተ፡ ሥላሴ፡ አመተ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ወለተ፡ መድኅን፡ ከመ፡ ይኲኖሙ፡ መርኃ፡ በምንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት። ለዓለም፡
                              ዓለም፡ አሜን።</q>
                           <note> The note mentions lǝǧ Gabra Kidān as the owner. Other members of
                              his family are also mentioned: his father Gabra Mikāʾel, his mother
                              Walatta Māryām, his brothers and sisters Gabra Māryām, Fǝre Qǝddus,
                              Gabra Masqal, Gabra Śǝllāse, Walatta Śǝllāse, ʾAmata Mikāʾel and
                              Walatta Madḫǝn. </note>
                        </item>

                        <item xml:id="e1">- Two notes written in a recent hand mention lǝǧ Gabra
                           Kidān as the donor of the Ms. to the church of Qǝddus Yoḥannǝs Maṭmǝq
                           (spelled "Kokolo" on <locus target="#40v">40v</locus>): <locus
                              target="#40r">40r</locus>, 40v. &#xD; - Omitted letters written
                           interlineally: <locus target="#7vb">7vb</locus>, 28rb, 31ra, 32va, 39rb,
                           39va.&#xD; - Corrections written over erased words and passages: <locus
                              target="#27vb">27vb</locus>.&#xD; - Erasures: <locus target="#39rb"
                              >39rb</locus>.&#xD; - Immediate corrections: repeated words or letters
                           encircled with black and red dots or crossed out in red ink, <locus
                              target="#7ra">7ra</locus>, 11ra, 12vb, 16ra.&#xD; - Tamallas-sign, in
                           the shape of a cross, indicating the place where an omitted word, written
                           in the upper margin, belongs: <locus target="#39vb">39vb</locus>.&#xD; -
                           Tamallas-sign, in the shape of two perpendicular lines, indicating the
                           place where an omitted word, written in the upper margin, belongs: <locus
                              target="#10vb">10vb</locus> (the omitted word is marked with a
                           decorative design), 39rb.&#xD; - Crude doodles of crosses, in recent
                           hand, in a blue pen: <locus target="#1v">1v</locus>, 2r, 40v.&#xD; -
                           Minor writings and scribbles in a blue pen: <locus target="#1r"
                              >1r</locus>, 2v, 2r, 40v.&#xD; - Pen trial: <locus target="#1r"
                              >1r</locus>, 3r, 40v.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>

